headline: Industrial stocks, not tech, may be next bubble, investor warns
summary: STORY: Shares of Genuine Auto Parts were "up 20% year to date until today's" quarterly earnings report, Lynch said, noting that the company missed Wall Street's estimates for profit and revenue and "issued weak guidance for the year."Shares tumbled as much as 14% on Tuesday.Shares of fellow industrials company Vulcan Materials were up about 15% so far in 2026, Lynch said, until it, too, delivered a lackluster earnings report on Tuesday.Its shares plummeted as much as 10% on Tuesday."So there's a wide disconnect between excitement and narratives about some of these, kind of, traditional, old-school, boring, non-AI names and what their fundamentals were actually delivering," Lynch said.
